cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict the argumenthood of prepositional phrases in English. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses pretrained word embeddings and other linguistically informed features, indicating a focus on machine learning, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions performance gains on semantic role labeling (SRL), which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories.
